# Fluid components — museothyssen

## Principle

**SDCs are fluid by default.** Layout (region template, page, paragraph wrapper, or parent grid) defines `max-width`, columns, and `gap`. The component defines internal structure, padding, and style — not fixed widths except in exceptions.

Block containers in Twig (`div`, `article`, `section`) already fill the parent width. Do not add `w-full` by default.

## Responsibilities

| Layer | Location | Defines | Does not define |
|------|-----------|--------|-----------|
| **SDC** | `components/*/*.twig` | Internal structure, padding, block typography | Page `max-w-*`, site columns |
| **Theme layout** | `templates/region--*.twig`, `page.html.twig` | Container, grid/flex, `gap` | Internal promo/hero styles |
| **Paragraph / block** | `templates/paragraphs/`, `templates/block/` | Drupal wrapper, spacing between blocks | Duplicate SDC markup |

## ✅ Correct

```twig
{# Fluid SDC — no fixed width on root #}
<article{{ attributes.addClass('museothyssen-card rounded-xl bg-white p-6') }}>
  {{ content }}
</article>
```

```twig
{# Layout defines distribution #}
<div class="layout-content mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
    {% for card in cards %}
      {{ card }}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</div>
```

`promo_banner` uses `lg:max-w-[50%]` on the **copy column**, not on the banner root — valid pattern for split hero, not for generic atoms.

## ❌ Incorrect

```twig
{# Fixed width on a reusable atom #}
<article class="w-[350px] ...">

{# Redundant #}
<div class="w-full">
```

## Exceptions

- **Icons / decorative media**: fixed sizes or `max-h-*` for aspect ratio.
- **Inline CTA** (`action_link`): `shrink-0`, `inline-flex`, design-fixed height (`h-[52px]`).
- **Images**: `object-cover` / `max-h-*` on the figure, not on the page wrapper.

## Tailwind

Responsive layout utilities belong in the **same markup** (`flex flex-col lg:flex-row`), not in duplicated `hidden lg:block` trees — see `ui/responsive-layouts.mdc`.
